Description: Outstanding example of a 1980's Westone Dynasty XV2RD (Red) in near mint condition. It functions flawlessly, no finish checking, horns, head stock, neck, body all near perfect. The most interesting thing to me is the Westone brochure that was in the case that has the name, address, and phone of the store purchased AND the date of purchase. It's in great condition and provides a history one does not normally find. A new set of Elixir 9's or 10' your choice come with the purchase. Westone is a wonderful manufacturer of fine instruments and have a great reputation. I am only selling because of age and want to downsize my "collection". The guitar has never left my home and was only played to maintain stability and keep everything functional. Search youtube for Westone Dynasty and listen. Great Guitar. Westone Dynasty (XV2)Body - solid Maple Neck - Hard Maple Fingerboard- Rosewood, graphite nutScale/frets - 25.5 inch, 22 fretBendmaster FT trem with locking nutH/S/H pickup configuration (Magnaflux II UBC/Magnaflux IV/Magnaflux II UBC) 3 way switch for the humbuckers, master volume pot has a push-pull switch for coil tap, tone 1 has a push-pull switch to activate the centre pickup and tone 2 has a switch to adjust phase on the bridge pickup.Available in red (XV2RD), white with red graphics (XV2SW) or black (XV2JB)
